variation.name: Creates a fail case when the element NetCashProvidedByUsedInFinancingActivitiesContinuingOperations is reported and disc ops is not reported in the cash flow statement.
variation.description:
Creates the following fail case: This rule refelects updated guidance from the Data Quality Committee which contradicts with historical rules. This is a change based on the changes in the cashflow ASU published by FASB.
 The element NetCashProvidedByUsedInFinancingActivitiesContinuingOperations has been reported with a value of 9,307. However no value has been reported for either the element(s) NetCashProvidedByUsedInFinancingActivities and CashProvidedByUsedInFinancingActivitiesDiscontinuedOperations. 
It is expected that if the element NetCashProvidedByUsedInFinancingActivitiesContinuingOperations is reported then values would be reported for these corresponding elements. If the value of 9,307 represents the value of NetCashProvidedByUsedInFinancingActivities then this more general element should be used as it is a required disclosure.

The properties of the fact associated with the element NetCashProvidedByUsedInFinancingActivitiesContinuingOperations are:
